1. Detailed Domain Description

The Inventory Management System (IMS) is designed to handle core stock transactionsâ€”receiving, selling, transferring, and adjusting inventory. The goal is to ensure stock levels are up to date and accurate across all locations.

The domain includes:

Products: Items that are bought, sold, or stored.

Locations: Physical areas where products are stored (warehouses, stores).

Transactions: Any activity that changes stock quantity.

Users (Optional): If roles or access control is needed.
